## Vendored NanoVM runtime

The SDK vendors the NanoVM browser runtime (`container/nanovm.mjs`,
`container/memfs.mjs`) and ships the NanoVM WebAssembly artifact. The copyright
in NanoVM is held by And The Next GmbH; as the rights holder it licenses that
runtime under MPL-2.0 within this SDK, even though the public `userland-run/nano`
repository is offered under AGPL-3.0 (see spec §13 — relicensing is a
rights-holder decision).

## Transitively bundled guest binaries

The NanoVM WebAssembly artifact embeds unmodified upstream RISC-V binaries
(BusyBox — GPL-2.0-only; Node.js — MIT-style; and the devenv toolchain) that run
as guest programs under emulation. See the NOTICE in `userland-run/nano` for the
full list and their licenses.
